article.headline: New Mexico St. 90, Pepperdine 66
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- Jahmar Young scored 21 points and Wendell McKines had six of his 18 points during a key 16-2 second-half run, leading New Mexico State to a 90-66 win over Pepperdine on Friday night. Jonathan Gibson scored 20 points and Troy Gillenwater had 19 for the Aggies (2-1). Gillenwater made a 3-point basket for a 77-61 lead and Gibson followed on New Mexico State's next possession with another 3-pointer at the 4-minute mark as the Aggies pulled away. Taylor Darby led the Waves (1-3) with 12 points and 11 rebounds. It was the first meeting between the two schools since Pepperdine's 84-69 NIT victory in 1989.
